such as watching HD live broadcast video or transmitting HDR photos, service providers keep continuously preparing for the upcoming high-end services like 4K/8K TV video and AR/VR application. Focusing on supplying service providers and system integrators no-new-wire or no-re-wiring residential networking solutions, SendTek Corporation announces today the newest 2Gbps Coax MDU Solution(CEM839/CES833/CES833N) for the booming demand of advanced value-added broadband services.</p> <br><p>SendTek’s G.hn based 2Gbps Coax MDU Solution is designed especially for service providers to upgrade or deploy their bundle service packages in hotel, condominium or residential apartment, with the least cost investment and the shortest installation time by simply utilizing existing coaxial cabling. By a featured CMTS-alike management system, service provider can efficiently administrate and operate the network for providing services. With Wi-Fi endpoint models, users can get connected seamlessly anytime anywhere inside the room or the housing. </p><br><p>For detail information, please contact SendTek by e-mail at <a href="mailto:sales@sendtek.com" target="_blank">sales@sendtek.com</a> or by phone at +886-3-567-8686.</p>													</div>					</li><!--newsaccordion--></div><p><img src="images/line.png" ></p><div id="item2"> <ul>	<li>September, 2018 – G.hn 2Gbps Coax Home Networking Bridge Announced</li> 	<li>September, 2018 – 2Gbps Coax MDU Solution Announced</li> 	 <li>October, 2015 – Gigabit Coax MDU Solution Announced</li><li>June, 2015 – HomeGrid Forum G.hn Certification Passed</li>   <li>December, 2014 – G.hn Wi-Fi Gigabit Ethernet Bridges Announced</li>    <li>December, 2014 – G.hn Phoneline Gigabit Ethernet Bridge Announced</li>    <li>September, 2014 – G.hn Coax Gigabit Ethernet Bridge Announced</li>    <li>2013 – HomePlug AV over Coax based EoC MDU Solution Announced</li><li>2012 – HomePNA3.1 based EoC MDU WiFi Endpoint Announced </li><li>2011 – HomePNA3.